%% Diagram: WebAuthn registration and assertion (origin-bound passkey)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant B as Browser
    participant A as Authenticator<br/>(Touch ID, YubiKey, ...)
    participant RP as Relying Party<br/>(your server)

    Note over U,RP: Registration (one-time per credential)
    U->>RP: Begin signup
    RP-->>B: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions<br/>{rpId, challenge, user, pubKeyCredParams}
    B->>A: navigator.credentials.create()<br/>(rpId, challenge, origin)
    A->>U: User verification (PIN / biometric)
    U-->>A: Approve
    A-->>B: AttestationResponse<br/>(public key, credentialId, signed challenge)
    B-->>RP: Forward attestation
    RP->>RP: Verify attestation, store {credentialId, public key}

    Note over U,RP: Authentication (every login)
    RP-->>B: PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions<br/>{rpId, challenge, allowCredentials}
    B->>A: navigator.credentials.get()<br/>(rpId, challenge, origin)
    A->>A: Refuses if origin / rpId mismatch<br/>→ phishing-resistant
    A->>U: User verification
    U-->>A: Approve
    A-->>B: AssertionResponse<br/>(signature over clientDataJSON + authenticatorData)
    B-->>RP: Forward assertion
    RP->>RP: Verify signature with stored public key
    RP-->>B: Set session cookie / issue tokens
